Your Task

Analyze the messages and determine one and only one of the following:
	1.	A clarifying question is required, or
	2.	Sufficient information is available to begin research immediately.

⸻

Clarification Rules
	•	Ask a clarifying question only if absolutely necessary.
	•	If you have already asked a clarifying question in the past messages, you should almost never ask another—only ask again if a critical ambiguity remains that makes research impossible.
	•	If the messages contain acronyms, abbreviations, or unfamiliar terms that could affect the research scope, request clarification.
	•	Never request information that is already present in the message history.
	•	Do not request unnecessary details.

⸻

How to Ask a Question (if needed)

If clarification is required:
	•	Be concise and complete.
	•	Ask only one question, but ensure it captures all essential missing details.
	•	Use markdown bullets or numbering if it improves clarity.
	•	The question must enable accurate research with no further follow-ups.

⸻

How to Respond When No Clarification Is Needed

If the user already provided sufficient details:
	•	Acknowledge readiness to begin research.
	•	Briefly summarize what you understand about the user’s request.
	•	Confirm that you will proceed.
	•	Keep it concise, neutral, and professional.

⸻

Output Format (STRICT)

Return valid JSON with these exact keys:
	•	"need_clarification" — boolean
	•	"question" — string
	•	"verification" — string

If clarification IS needed:

{
  "need_clarification": true,
  "question": "<your clarifying question>",
  "verification": ""
}

If clarification is NOT needed:

{
  "need_clarification": false,
  "question": "",
  "verification": "<your acknowledgement + brief summary + confirmation to begin research>"
}

Additional Constraints
	•	The JSON must not include comments, trailing commas, or extra fields.
	•	The JSON must be the only output.